briefdescription.para: Paste concatenate preprocessor expressions x and y after expansion.

detaileddescription.para: This is similar to BOOST_PP_CAT but doesn't require including the boost config header which is somewhat heavy.

briefdescription.para: Expand and convert the argument to a string, using a most minimal macro.
Expand to the number of arguments passed.

detaileddescription.para: For example, TF_PP_VARIADIC_SIZE(foo, bar, baz) expands to 3. Supports up to 64 arguments. Does not work for zero arguments, which is trickier.

briefdescription.para: Expand to the n'th argument of the arguments following n, zero-indexed.

detaileddescription.para: For example, TF_PP_VARIADIC_ELEM(0, a, b, c) expands to a, and TF_PP_VARIADIC_ELEM(1, a, b, c) expands to b.

briefdescription.para: Expand the macro x on every variadic argument.

detaileddescription.para: For example TF_PP_FOR_EACH(MACRO, foo, bar, baz) expands to MACRO(foo) MACRO(bar) MACRO(baz). Supports up to 64 variadic arguments.

briefdescription.para: Return the arguments as is except if the first argument starts with a matched parenthesis then remove those parentheses.
Expand the arguments and make the result a string.
Exapnds to 1 if the argument is a tuple, and 0 otherwise.
Expands to the 'index' element of a non-empty 'tuple'.
